<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFDFFBCFC959F0D6C5E797F" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFC959F0D6D5E7EE1" blockId="16.[831,1437,840,1054]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFC959F0D6ABD7E00" bold="true" box="[831,944,841,865]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Remarks:</emphasis>
The more elongated triserial portion distinguishes this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFC959FC36C5E797F" blockId="16.[831,1437,840,1054]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFC959FC36D7C7EFE" bold="true" box="[831,1137,903,927]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was originally described from the Dano-Montian of 
<collectingCountry id="32CB7663FFFDFFBCFBDA9FE36DCE7EDE" box="[1136,1219,935,959]" name="Algeria" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Algeria</collectingCountry>
. It is also recorded in the lowermost Paleocene of northern Sinai (SAID &amp; KENAWY, 1956). In the study area, it is recorded in the Maastrichtian and the Early Paleocene sediments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
